The robot's speed is constant. Therefore, the time it takes to travel a certain distance is inversely proportional to the distance traveled. We set up a proportion to find the length of the hallway: \begin{align*}
2.5\text{ hours}&:1\text{ km} \\
90\text{ seconds}&:x\text{ meters}
\end{align*} Since we know that $90$ seconds is $1/2$ hour, we can write the proportion as: \begin{align*}
2.5\text{ hours}&:1\text{ km} \\
\frac{1}{2}\text{ hour}&:x\text{ meters}
\end{align*} Since the ratios of the two quantities are inversely proportional, we know that $\frac{1}{2}=\frac{2.5}{x}$. Solving for $x$ gives $x=\frac{2.5\times2}{1}=\frac{5}{2}=\boxed{2.5}$ meters.รถยนต์
